{"sha": "f1ad7bac76b662577e3bde78c530954099361a66", "node_id": "MDY6Q29tbWl0MTM2NTMxMDA6ZjFhZDdiYWM3NmI2NjI1NzdlM2JkZTc4YzUzMDk1NDA5OTM2MWE2Ng==", "commit": {"author": {"name": "Jason Merrill", "email": "jason@redhat.com", "date": "2020-04-04T15:04:55Z"}, "committer": {"name": "Jason Merrill", "email": "jason@redhat.com", "date": "2020-04-04T15:06:31Z"}, "message": "c++: Fix invalid pointer-to-member in requires [PR67825]\n\nA recent change to cmcstl2 led to two tests failing due to this bug: our\nvalid expression checking in the context of a requires-expression wasn't\ncatching that an expression of member function type can only appear as the\nfunction operand of a call expression.  Fixed by using convert_to_void to do\nthe same checking as a discarded-value expression.\n\nThis patch also fixes 67825, which already had a testcase, but the testcase\nwas testing for the wrong behavior.\n\ngcc/cp/ChangeLog\n2020-04-04  Jason Merrill  <jason@redhat.com>\n\n\tPR c++/67825\n\t* constraint.cc (tsubst_valid_expression_requirement): Call\n\tconvert_to_void.", "tree": {"sha": "004cc66d52a4f6c00c0f39cfce25b563cb6a8421", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/git/trees/004cc66d52a4f6c00c0f39cfce25b563cb6a8421"}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/git/commits/f1ad7bac76b662577e3bde78c530954099361a66", "comment_count": 0, "verification": {"verified": false, "reason": "unsigned", "signature": null, "payload": null}}, "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commits/f1ad7bac76b662577e3bde78c530954099361a66", "html_url": "https://github.com/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commit/f1ad7bac76b662577e3bde78c530954099361a66", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Rust-GCC/gccrs/commits/f1ad7bac76b662577e3bde78c530954099361a66/comments", "author": {"login": "jicama", "id": 266146, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjI2NjE0Ng==", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/266146?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/jicama", "html_url"